executor_description: Gets Signal Tree Node by name. This API can also be used to get all the Nodes for a requested Signal Tree in an account.

queryParams.description: Name of the Signal Tree Node. By default, it performs a contains match. To match the exact name, set the value with double quotes.
Index to start for the next paginated request. Default value is 0.
Number of items to include in each page result. There could be fewer items remaining than the specified value.

executor_description: Gets Signal Tree by name. This API can also be used to get all the Signal Trees in an account.

queryParams.description: Name of the Signal Tree. By default, it performs a contains match. To match the exact name, set the value with double quotes.
State of the Signal Tree. By default, latest as well as published versions of the Signal Tree will be returned. To only get the latest version, set the value as DRAFT.
This is a mandatory field. Reports in Falkonry are also organized in a tree-like structures and use similar layout structure. Set the value of this field to SIGNAL to look for only Signal Trees.
Index to start for the next paginated request. Default value is 0.
Number of items to include in each page result. There could be fewer items remaining than the specified value.

Index to start for the next paginated request. Default value is 0.
Number of items to include in each page result. There could be fewer items remaining than the specified value.

executor_description: Get an Entity by ID within an account.

The output data is in the form of Predictions, Episodes, Confidence Score and Explanation Score. Each type of output data has its own identity and endpoint. Signal Data API can be used to retrieve the data for Predictions, Confidence Score and Explanation Score. Each output data type is referenced as Connected Source with an unique identity for each entity. This Connected Source ID can be found in Live Context object.

executor_description: Gets Episode list within an account. This API can be used to get all Episodes or filter by datastream, assessment and model.

queryParams.description: Filter the Episodes by type. Set this to NOVEL to get Novel Episodes or set this to NOTIFICATION to get Alert type Episodes.
Filter the Episodes by status. Set this to OPEN to get open Episodes or set this to ASSIGNED to get resolved Episodes.
Filter the Episodes that are ready for review. Set this to true to get Episodes ready for review.
Filter the Episodes by Datastream. Set this to Datastream ID. For multiple Datastreams, set datastream param in multiple.
Filter the Episodes by Assessment. Set this to Assessment ID. For multiple Assessments, set assessment param in multiple.
Filter the Episodes by Model. Set this to Model ID. For multiple Models, set model param in multiple.
Filter the Episodes by Entity. Set this to Entity ID. For multiple Entities, set entity param in multiple.
Index to start for the next paginated request. Default value is 0.
Number of items to include in each page result. There could be fewer items remaining than the specified value.
Sort the items by time. Set this to -createTime to get the latest item first.
Expand the details of the allowed properties. Set this to predictedCondition to get the Condition label. Allowed properties are: entity, predictedCondition, model and latestDispositionCondition.
